---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Rodent Control for Restaurants NYC & NJ | Cloakd"
  description="A single rodent sighting is a critical DOHMH violation. The 90-day fertility management program that puts consistent distance between your kitchen and that outcome."
  path="/solutions/restaurants"
>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── HERO ── -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-24 px-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">
        Restaurants &amp; Food Service
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-8">
        Paid for pest control last month.<br />
        Whether your NYC restaurant passes the next inspection depends on the timing.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-10">
        One rat sighting is a critical DOHMH rodent violation — 5 points
        minimum, up to $2,000 in fines, and a B in your window. If that visit
        falls in week six after your last treatment, the new colony is already
        rebuilding. The 90-day program closes that window.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/get-started"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold rounded bg-[#b85530] text-[#faf8f4] hover:bg-[#c96a3a] transition-colors"
      >
        Start the 90-day program
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── THE INSPECTION MATH ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        What a violation actually costs
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        One sighting. One inspection. The math gets bad fast.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 max-w-xl mb-16 leading-relaxed">
        NYC DOHMH conducts unannounced inspections. Each inspection produces
        a score that determines your restaurant's letter grade. You do not
        get to prepare for the visit. You either have the problem under
        control or you don't.
      </p>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-12">
        {[
          {
            value: '5+',
            unit: 'points',
            label: 'minimum per rodent violation',
            sub: 'Codes 04K (rats) and 04L (mice) are critical violations under NYC DOHMH',
            color: '#c96a3a',
          },
          {
            value: '14',
            unit: 'points',
            label: 'is all it takes for a B grade',
            sub: 'One rodent violation combined with any other critical puts a B in your window',
            color: '#c96a3a',
          },
          {
            value: '$2,000',
            unit: 'max',
            label: 'fine per rodent violation',
            sub: 'NYC rodent violations carry fines from $300 to $2,000 per citation',
            color: '#c96a3a',
          },
          {
            value: '$50K',
            unit: 'lost',
            label: 'revenue from one closure',
            sub: 'A temporary closure in NYC costs $15,000 to $50,000 in lost revenue',
            color: '#c96a3a',
          },
        ].map(({ value, unit, label, sub, color }) => (
          <div class="bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8 rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-1 mb-3">
              <span class="text-4xl font-bold" style={`color:${color}`}>{value}</span>
              <span class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814]/55">{unit}</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] leading-snug mb-2">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8 rounded-xl p-6 max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">
          NJ restaurants face equivalent exposure under state health code. The
          inspection system differs from NYC's letter grading, but the financial
          consequences of a rodent citation — remediation costs, reinspection
          fees, public record, and reputational damage — are comparable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHY IT KEEPS HAPPENING ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
            The real problem
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
            Your exterminator treats what's there. The problem is what moves in after they leave.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Standard treatment removes the colony that's present. The kitchen
            goes clean. The vendor leaves. Within 4 to 8 weeks, surrounding
            rats detect the empty territory and a new group moves in. The food
            source hasn't changed. The entry points haven't changed. The cycle
            resets before your next scheduled visit.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            For a restaurant, this means every inspection is a timing game.
            If the health inspector arrives in week two after a treatment,
            you're fine. Week six, you're exposed. There's no version of
            standard pest control that removes that variable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            { week: 'Week 1–2', status: 'clean', label: 'Treatment complete. Active population removed. Clean kitchen.' },
            { week: 'Week 3–4', status: 'watch', label: 'Territory sits empty. Surrounding colonies detect vacancy.' },
            { week: 'Week 5–6', status: 'risk', label: 'New group moves in. Population rebuilding at full fertility.' },
            { week: 'Week 7–8', status: 'risk', label: 'New colony established. Back to the same baseline.' },
            { week: 'Week 9+', status: 'reset', label: 'Next treatment visit. Cycle resets. Same problem, same cost.' },
          ].map(({ week, status, label }) => (
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
              <div class={`flex-shrink-0 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold ${
                status === 'clean'
                  ? 'bg-[#7aab7e]/15 text-[#5e9263]'
                  : status === 'watch'
                  ? 'bg-[#d4a843]/15 text-[#c09530]'
                  : 'bg-[#c96a3a]/15 text-[#b85530]'
              }`}>
                {week}
              </div>
              <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed pt-0.5">{label}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── HOW THE PROGRAM WORKS ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        How it works for restaurants
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        Two layers. Your existing vendor stays in place.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 max-w-xl mb-16 leading-relaxed">
        We don't replace your current pest control setup. We add an integrated
        pest management layer on top of it, addressing what knockdown alone cannot.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8 rounded-xl p-8">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 mb-6">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#d4a843] bg-[#d4a843]/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Phase 1</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[#1c1814]/55">Handled by your existing vendor</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Remove what's there</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Your current pest control vendor handles immediate knockdown. We
            coordinate directly with them to establish a clean baseline before
            Phase 2 begins. No contract changes, no displacement.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/55 leading-relaxed">
            Produces the visible evidence — dead rodents removed, entry points
            assessed — that satisfies an inspector and your staff.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-[#7aab7e]/25 rounded-xl p-8">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 mb-6">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#7aab7e] bg-[#7aab7e]/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Phase 2</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[#1c1814]/55">Cloakd — fertility management</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Stop the replacement colony</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Evolve bait stations are placed in back-of-house, storage areas,
            and along known travel paths. Evolve is derived from cottonseed
            and carries EPA minimum risk designation — cleared for use in
            food-handling environments. Rats that consume it reproduce at a
            fraction of their normal rate, and over a single breeding cycle the
            replacement population can't form at full size.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/55 leading-relaxed">
            No secondary kill risk to staff, customers, or wildlife. Safe for
            continuous deployment in active kitchens.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[#e8e0d0] rounded-xl p-6 border border-[#1c1814]/5">
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">
          Phase 1 removes the current population while Phase 2 prevents the
          next colony from forming at full capacity. Over 90 days, documented
          track counts show the population declining rather than cycling. That
          documentation goes with you into any inspection.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── PROOF ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        Field data
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-16 max-w-2xl">
        Numbers from monitored urban deployments
      </h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        {[
          { value: '79%', label: 'reduction in rodent track presence', sub: 'Location A — 5-month urban field study, Aug 2025 to Jan 2026', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '88%', label: 'drop in track density at the same site', sub: 'Tracks per monitoring plate declined even where rodents were still present', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '90%', label: 'fertility reduction potential', sub: 'When Evolve is integrated into an active pest management program', color: '#c96a3a' },
        ].map(({ value, label, sub, color }) => (
          <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-5xl font-bold mb-3" style={`color:${color}`}>{value}</p>
            <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] leading-snug mb-2">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
        Field studies across two independent urban deployment sites. At the
        city level: NYC began deploying ContraPest in rat mitigation zones
        in April 2025. Baltimore adopted Evolve for its city rodent control
        program the same year.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── CTA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
          Start before the next inspection.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          The program takes 90 days to produce documented results. The sooner
          it starts, the more distance you have before the inspector walks in.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a
            href="/get-started"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold rounded bg-[#b85530] text-[#faf8f4] hover:bg-[#c96a3a] transition-colors"
          >
            Start the 90-day program
          </a>
          <a
            href="/how-it-works"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            How it works
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
